An accident that happened along Olokuta/Shasha Road in Akure, Ondo State has claimed four people, including a commercial driver. The accident was reportedly caused by a head-on collision between an Ore-bound bus and a Sienna space bus traveling from Ondo town. It was gathered that four victims lost their lives on the spot when the accident occurred. Other passengers who were stuck in the vehicles were rescued with the assistance of drivers and locals in the area.